AIM: 
To write a C program to check whether a given number is a prime number or not. 
 
 
ALGORITHM: 
1. Start the program. 
2. Declare variables n and i, and a flag variable isPrime. 
3. Read the number n from the user. 
4. If n is less than or equal to 1, set isPrime = 0 (not prime). 
5. Otherwise, set isPrime = 1 (assume prime). 
6. Loop from i = 2 to n/2: 
 If n is divisible by i, set isPrime = 0 and break the loop. 
7. If isPrime is 1, print "Prime number", else print "Not a prime number". 
8. Stop the program. 
 
 
PROGRAM: 
#include <stdio.h> 
int main() { 
int n, i, isPrime = 1; 
printf("Enter a number: "); 
scanf("%d", &n); 
if (n <= 1) { 
isPrime = 0; 
} else { 
for (i = 2; i <= n / 2; i++) { 
if (n % i == 0) { 
isPrime = 0; 
break; 
} 
}  
} 
if (isPrime == 1) 
printf("%d is a Prime number.\n", n); 
else 
printf("%d is Not a Prime number.\n", n); 
return 0; 
} 
 
 
SAMPLE OUTPUT: 
Enter a number: 7 
7 is a Prime number. 
Enter a number: 10 
10 is Not a Prime number.
